I've read all the posts, but still end up confused...<br>
<br>
Are the evil, called evil because they hate the good?<br>
Are the good, called good because they hate the evil?<br>
Are the neutral, called netural because they're neither good nor evil? /boggle<br>
Looks like an aviak and egg issue.<br>
<br>
I think the following model should make sense...<br>
<br>
Starting with the premise of evil:<br>
I always thought that being evil means doing things that hurt others (whether the others is good, neutral or evil). So an evil can jolly well fight evil too! <br>
The main aim of being evil is to bring as much pain to others as possible.<br>
<br>
Then, there will be good, because if you fight the evil doers, you are good!<br>
<br>
Or you can start with the premise of good:<br>
Means doing things that benefit others, that brings as much well being to others as possible.<br>
<br>
Then, there will be evil, because if you fight the do gooders, you are evil!<br>
<br>
Then what is neutral...hmm...doing things that do not help nor harm anyone? Doing things that harm and help others? Not doing anything? Goof off and eat and drink and be merry? <br>
Ah I think I got it -yes, being neutral is:<br>
Yes, you will fight evil, when necessary, i.e. When you are threatened by the evil...natural survival of the fittest...<br>
whilst the good have a vendetta against the evil.<br>
Now the problem is determining when you are actually threatened by evil...maybe that's why the druids at the circles attack the evils...because the answer is, EVERYONE is threatened by the evil, as the evil do harm to everyone.<br>
<br>
Then what is the difference between good and neutral...the difference is the mindset...the good pursue the evil to benefit others (do good mentality)...the neutral pursue the evil to remove the threat to themselves (survival of the fittest mentality)<br>
<br>
Now the problem is Verant blankets evil by the gods they worship or their races, so you can't control the NPCs reactions. <br>
But as for RP, we can control our own reactions. If you believe that reanimating the dead does not bring pain to the dead...then perhaps necromancers can be not evil. If you believe that the power to suck life does not bring much more agony to your prey than engulfing it in flames, then the method is not more evil than the other.<br>
<br>
Phew...I spent 15 mins thinking about that...had to get it out...I probably won't respond to any more posts in this thread...I hope...this is sucking waay too much of my time...Now THAT is evil...<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p><p style="line-height: 100%"><a href="http://eq.guildmagic.com/character.cfm?ID=208972"><font face="Comic Sans MS"><font color="#009933"><font size="5">c<font size="3" face="Comic Sans MS" color="#009933"><font size="5">aeo</font><font size="3">n</font><font size="5">a</font><font size="3">
