<br>
Death is far from the only truth, small one. Death is not the end, it is not final. You see, few creatures ever truly die.<br>
<br>
Many who leave thier mortal form become spirits who continue to effect and shape this world. Many are given another form of life after thier first expires. Some cheat death and become undead, forever evading it's grasp. And the actions we take in our life never die, they echo throughout eternity. <br>
<br>
While creatures can be slain, the actions they took remain behind, by slaying them you are merely preventing them from taking any further actions. <br>
<br>
There is much to be had and done in ones life, to merely spend it wallowing in the fact that you are one day going to die is pathetic. One does not need immortality to effect this world. Were that the case, Cazic-Thule would have made us Iksar immortal. <br>
<br>
I've thought about what you said when we first met gnome. And I've waited a long time to tell you what you made me realize. Death does come for us all. But we should not worship it. We Iksar should savor every moment of our lives Cazic-Thule has blessed us with, no matter how painful, and try and accomplish as much as we can, while we can. <p><img src="http://members.aol.com/bseh42/images/zilsig.jpg"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/uzildrax.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zildrax</A> at: 7/20/02 3:34:49 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ukimayasilverbark.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Kimaya Silverbark</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://prod.bsis.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/folders/6507/67125button-wolf-pawprint" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tao Te Bark</span><br>  Posts: 389<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(7/21/02 9:17:21 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm23.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=93.topic&index=47>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://home.bellsouth.net/coDataImages/p/Groups/15/15568/pages/34736/Kimaya-60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: green cloud?  death?  Laughter!</span><hr size=1> *claps for Zildrax*  Yay for savoring life!  *giggle!*<br>
